{"TopicId":165391,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Rover Wheels only steer a little","CreatedByName":"SpaceTrashCan","CreatedById":168889,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T14:35:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SpaceTrashCan","CreatedById":168889,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T14:35:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo i had thsi problem with a couple of my rovers lately. The wheels steer in thh right direction. But only so little. Does any\u00F3ne know what teh problem is. Is it the other parts right next to the wheels? Because i didn\u0027t have the problem with open wheel rovers. But on the other side ive built rovers with\u00A0wheel wells before and it worked just fine\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T15:11:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223170191\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165391\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505140557\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168889\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceTrashCan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, SpaceTrashCan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it the other parts right next to the wheels?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProabably. Wheels get steering reductions even from parts that are pretty far away and that would not touch the wheels even when fully steering.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s hard to tell\u00A0without a screenshot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-11T15:12:04Z\u0022 title=\u002209/11/2017 03:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Gaarst\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceTrashCan","CreatedById":168889,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T15:14:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022b6df96-1505142824.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.bilder-upload.eu/upload/b6df96-1505142824.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere ya go \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 I\u0027ve had this problem with a lot of different rover lately. \u00A0It does happen with wheels that are far from anything else too.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-11T15:19:50Z\u0022 title=\u002209/11/2017 03:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by SpaceTrashCan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T15:21:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Gameplay Questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T15:34:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you see the wheels steering? Lots of my rovers can be turned either using\u00A0the wheel steering or by using brute force from reaction wheels. If you are turning slowly it could be because you are using\u00A0the reaction wheels to turn instead of steering.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T16:03:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223170209\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165391\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505142854\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168889\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceTrashCan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, SpaceTrashCan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.bilder-upload.eu/upload/b6df96-1505142824.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022b6df96-1505142824.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.bilder-upload.eu/upload/b6df96-1505142824.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere ya go \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 I\u0027ve had this problem with a lot of different rover lately. \u00A0It does happen with wheels that are far from anything else too.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it\u0027s the fact that the wheel is close to the spoiler in front of it. You need to have quite some space between the wheels and the parts around it for them to steer properly, but even then it\u0027s sometimes weird: in the picture below the wheel (left front) steers further to the left\u00A0(backwards) than to the right (frontwards) even though it\u0027s closer to the beam behind it than to the elevon in front\u00A0of it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MHbEMvb.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022761\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/MHbEMvb.png\u0022 width=\u0022889\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-11T16:04:14Z\u0022 title=\u002209/11/2017 04:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Gaarst\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceTrashCan","CreatedById":168889,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T18:46:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank You for the Answers \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0Yeah, i haven\u0027t understood the logic that KSP uses for this yet. With the wheel further back, still didn\u00C4\u0027t turn properly.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut then again, with this car i had no problem with the wheels:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220170618224639_1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022418\u0022 src=\u0022https://www2.pic-upload.de/img/33361261/20170618224639_1.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223170222\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165391\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505144053\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257809\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tomf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, tomf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you see the wheels steering? Lots of my rovers can be turned either using\u00A0the wheel steering or by using brute force from reaction wheels. If you are turning slowly it could be because you are using\u00A0the reaction wheels to turn instead of steering.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat could be it! I\u0027m gonnac check this out. Thank You for the reply \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceTrashCan","CreatedById":168889,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T19:14:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223170222\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165391\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505144053\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257809\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tomf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, tomf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you see the wheels steering? Lots of my rovers can be turned either using\u00A0the wheel steering or by using brute force from reaction wheels. If you are turning slowly it could be because you are using\u00A0the reaction wheels to turn instead of steering.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nunfortunately is wasn\u0027t the reaction wheel. But Thank You for your answer anyway \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}